<p class="card-text">Abra is a province geographically located in the northern archipelago of Luzon particularly on the western side of the Cordillera, surrounded by Ilocos Norte and Apayao on the North, Mountain Province and Ilocos Sur on the South, Kalinga on the East and Ilocos Sur on the West. Abra is a majestic mountainous province and very rich in natural resources composing of rivers, lakes, water falls, caves and other tourist destinations that Abrenians can be proud of all over the world.

Long time ago, the province had been unpopular or a blank spot on the Philippine tourist map until it was discovered and gone viral by bloggers and adventurers who are posting online and through the social media and web logs. Adventurers, tourists and travelers are now starting to explore the landlocked province tourist spots destinations. Abra is often skipped by tourists because of its location which is very far from Manila and the province is also known as a political hotspot. But there is more to offer when you explore the province. It is surrounded by popular tourists destinations, such as: (1) Ilocos where the Vigan City, one of the Seven Wonders of the World, is located and (2) Cordillera in the east where Baguio City, the Summer Capital City of the Philippines, is situated. There are many tourist attractions which Abre≈àos can be proud of, that are still unknown.</p>
